<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Mental Health Report</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 18px;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background: linear-gradient(white,black); /* Background color for the website */
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
        }
        .page {
            background-color: #ffffff; /* Background color for the page */
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            max-width: 730px;
            width: 100%;
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
        }
        p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        h2 {
            margin-top: 30px;
        }
        ul {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }
        li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="page">
        <h1>Mental Health Report</h1>
        <p>This report is based on an analysis of your recent social media posts.</p>
        <h2>Overall Emotional Tone: {{dominant_emotion}} ({{dominant_score}})</h2>
        <p><b>{{dominant_emotion}}</b>: This is the most prominent emotion detected in your posts.</p>
        <h2>Emotional Breakdown</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Joy</b>: A score of {{joy_score}} indicates a {{joy_presence}} presence of joy in your posts.</li>
            <li><b>Sadness</b>: A score of {{sadness_score}} indicates a {{sadness_presence}} presence of sadness in your posts.</li>
            <li><b>Anger</b>: A score of {{anger_score}} indicates a {{anger_presence}} presence of anger in your posts.</li>
            <li><b>Fear</b>: A score of {{fear_score}} indicates a {{fear_presence}} presence of fear in your posts.</li>
            <li><b>Neutral</b>: A score of {{neutral_score}} indicates a {{neutral_presence}} presence of neutral sentiment in your posts.</li>
        </ul>

    </div>
</body>
</html>
